CREATIVE ACHIEVEMENTS
It is important to utilise the most relevant and up to date information and so a large proportion
of time is dedicated to research. During the Master’s course, researching different design
guidelines and human computer interaction theories allowed for the work to develop at a
constant rate, using researched knowledge to overcome problems.
To date, grades indicate a Masters with distinction.
General Approach
A student led project with Tate Britain to increase interaction from all the visiting public.
Worked with Tate Britain staff to explore the brief. Designed solutions to specifically
encourage the casual visitor to interact with art.
Tate Britain (Chelsea College of Art and Design)
Responsible for website and production of a highly successful digital message board that
encouraged visitors to share feedback by text and twitter.
Student led project to encourage collaboration between art and science students, with the aim
of sharing knowledge and skills.
Responsible for developing a website based on the principles of facebook that students used
as a forum to share, learn and produce collaborative work.
Imperial College London and Chelsea College of Art and Design,
Created multiple artworks, developing bespoke software, combined with industry standard
production tools, to write programs that interacted with the users. The interaction was based
around the users physical information , producing sounds and drawings specific to the individual.
Used a selection of hardware and software options to create the artwork. Hacked and created
hardware for specific use, along side open hardware like Arduino.
Developed a small blimp which was produced from a wireless security camera. It followed
members of the audience around a gallery space.
Developed an interactive documentary on privacy and network computing, which displayed
a selection of sourced material to the user, depending on certain criteria with each viewing
changing the user experience.
Adapted the documentary to a large touch screen table to allow users to browse in a more
user friendly manner
